ig": {\n      "tp": 1,\n      "pp": 1,\n      "dp": 1,\n      "max_model_len": 4096,\n      "quantization": null,\n      "dtype": "auto",\n      "kv_cache_dtype": "fp8",\n      "chunked_prefill": true,\n      "prefix_caching": true,\n      "enforce_eager": false,\n      "scheduling_policy": "lpm",\n      "mem_fraction_static": 0.9,\n      "max_running_requests": null,\n      "max_prefill_tokens": 4096,\n      "schedule_policy": "lpm",\n      "continuous_decode_steps": 1\n    },\n    "peak_throughput": 0.0,\n    "ttft_p95": 0.0,\n    "tpot_p95": 0.0,\n    "smoke_pass": "0/3",\n    "classification": "none"\n  },\n  {\n    "id": "77a7f5c35600",\n    "engine": "vllm",\n    "status": "success",\n    "config": {\n      "tp": 1,\n      "pp": 1,\n      "dp": 1,\n      "max_model_len": 4096,\n      "quantization": null,\n      "dtype": "auto",\n      "kv_cache_dtype": "auto",\n      "chunked_prefill": false,\n      "prefix_caching": false,\n      "enforce_eager": false,\n      "scheduling_policy": "fcfs",\n      "gpu_mem_util": 0.9,\n      "max_num_seqs": 256,\n      "max_num_batched_tokens": null\n    },\n    "peak_throughput": 0.0,\n    "ttft_p95": 0.0,\n    "tpot_p95": 0.0,\n    "smoke_pass": "1/3",\n    "classification": "none"\n  }\n]\n\n## Best Results So Far\n- Best throughput: 0.0 tok/s (config: )\n- Best latency (TTFT p95): inf ms (config: )\n- Best balanced: throughput=0.0, latency=inf (config: )\n\n## Experiment Count\n3 / 30\n\n## Rules\n1. For the FIRST 3-5 experiments, try baseline configs: default params with TP=1, TP=max_gpus for both vllm and sglang.\n2. After baselines, analyze trends and try improvements based on the optimization goal.\n3. If goal is "optimize_throughput": focus on batching, DP, quantization, high concurrency.\n4. If goal is "optimize_latency": focus on TP, enforce_eager, lower batch sizes.\n5. If goal is "optimize_balanced": find configs where TTFT p95 < 500.0 ms AND throughput is maximized.\n6. If goal is "explore": try something new — different engine, quantization, speculative decoding.\n7. Never repeat an exact configuration that was already tested.\n8. max_model_len must not exceed 4096.\n9. tensor_parallel_size must divide evenly into 1 GPUs.\n\n## Best Practices\n- vLLM: chunked prefill + prefix caching works well together for throughput.\n- SGLang: radix cache (prefix caching) is ON by default. lpm schedule policy benefits from prefix caching.\n- fp8 quantization usually gives ~1.5-2x throughput with minimal quality loss.\n- Higher gpu_memory_utilization (0.95) allows more KV cache but risks OOM.\n- data_parallel_size > 1 is great for throughput when model fits in fewer GPUs.\n- enforce_eager=true in vLLM can reduce latency for small batches.\n- num_continuous_decode_steps > 1 in SGLang reduces scheduling overhead.\n\n## User Instructions\nДополнительно оцени какой прирост даст MTP\n`python -m sglang.launch_server --model-path Qwen/Qwen3.5-9B --port 8000 --tp-size 1 --mem-fraction-static 0.8 --context-length 262144 --reasoning-parser qwen3 --speculative-algo NEXTN --speculative-num-steps 3 --speculative-eagle-topk 1 --speculative-num-draft-tokens 4`\nА для vllm оцени какой прирост дает --language-model-only\n\n\nGenerate the next experiment configuration.\n', 'role': 'system'}, {'content': 'Generate the next experiment configuration.', 'role': 'user'}], 'model': 'zai-org/GLM-4.6', 'response_format': {'type': 'json_schema', 'json_schema': {'schema': {'description': 'Schema for the Planner LLM response.', 'properties': {'engine': {'description': "Engine to use: 'vllm' or 'sglang'", 'title': 'Engine', 'type': 'string'}, 'tensor_parallel_size': {'default': 1, 'description': 'Tensor parallelism size', 'title': 'Tensor Parallel Size', 'type': 'integer'}, 'pipeline_parallel_size': {'default': 1, 'description': 'Pipeline parallelism size', 'title': 'Pipeline Parallel Size', 'type': 'integer'}, 'data_parallel_size': {'default': 1, 'description': 'Data parallelism size', 'title': 'Data Parallel Size',